The paper discusses query optimization in big data management, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of probability and uncertainty in query completeness also suggests relevance to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed Probery system utilizes machine learning techniques, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
